title: Grateful Dead Live at Pyramid Arena on 1995-04-01
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, Candyman, Take Me To The River*, Lazy River Road, When I Paint My Masterpiece**, Childhood's End, Deal

Set 2

Foolish Heart, Way To Go Home-> Saint Of Circumstance, Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Space-> The Wheel-> All Along The Watchtower-, Standing On the Moon, E: One More Saturday Night

* First time played, ** Weir on acoustic

reviews.review_text:
Grateful Dead's 2nd Time in Memphis Hard to believe this is the GD's second concert in Memphis, the last time being in 1970 (!)  The crowd is ready for them, and judging by the enthusiastic reception to every song, it's easy to imagine that the band could have played just about anything this night.

What we do get is a nice, laid-back, bluesy set.  The first set is interesting for the first ever "Take Me to the River" (that's right, the Talking Heads song), and "When I Paint My Masterpiece" is especially powerful here.

The second set is in the same vein, punctuated by the type of long, otherworldly "Drums/Space" that had become prevalent this Spring.  There's some really great stuff going on here.  Vince had been trying to tease "The Wheel" during "Space" for about two weeks leading up to this, and tonight, the rest of the band is in there with him.  This leads into Watchtower > Standing on the Moon, which is at least the second time they did this combo.  And it really works!  Not a raucous set, but made memorable between what's going on between the band and the crowd.
